					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In <a href="http://pineight.com/nes/#ruder" class="postlink">Zap Ruder</a>, my Zapper experiment ROM, the "zapkernels" are responsible for measuring how far down the screen the Zapper is pointed. What they do is add 256*2/3 to a variable every scanline and use BCS to waste an average two-thirds of a cycle in the branch taken penalty.
<br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; clc<br />&nbsp; lda subcycle<br />&nbsp; adc #$AA<br />&nbsp; sta subcycle<br />&nbsp; bcs :+<br />:<br /></div>
<br />That said, I'm working on collecting some pictures to make a slideshow ROM.</div>

